  "summary": "Empty placeholder package on PyPI mimicking Nagios XI product name",
  "details": "The package ships no executable code: no setup.py, no __init__.py, no package modules, and no entry points or build hooks. Only pyproject.toml metadata, an empty README, and egg-info are present, with build-backend set to setuptools.build_meta and no extensions. The distribution name mimics the commercial Nagios XI product, and the author email (pocbug@protonmail.com) suggests a proof-of-concept or name-reservation publication rather than a functioning library. Because the package is empty, installing or importing it cannot exfiltrate data, execute remote code, or otherwise harm the installer; the only risk is developer confusion if the name is mistaken for an official Nagios XI integration.",
